---
description: Public-safety rules for MichaelOS — no secrets, no private data in the repo
alwaysApply: true
---

# Public-safe by default

- Never commit `.env`, real API keys, webhook URLs, or personal data.
- The real Vault lives outside the repo; only `VAULT_PATH` placeholder in `.env.example`.
- Tests and demos use the committed Demo vault at `examples/demo-vault/` only.
- Run logs go to gitignored `./.logs/`; runtime state to `.mastra/`.
- Use `.env.example` for documenting env vars; never real values.
